article.description: — Lucas Williamson had a career-high 27 points as Loyola Chicago topped Illinois State 78-64 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Williamson leads Loyola Chicago past Illinois St. 78-64
article.linkText: Williamson leads Loyola Chicago past Illinois St. 78-64
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Lucas Williamson had a career-high 27 points as Loyola Chicago topped Illinois State 78-64 on Wednesday night. Williamson made 6 of 9 3-pointers. Ryan Schwieger had 18 points for Loyola Chicago (17-4, 8-2 Missouri Valley Conference). Loyola Chicago dominated the first half and led 42-22 at the break. The Redbirds' 22 points in the first half marked a season low for the team. Antonio Reeves had 20 points for the Redbirds (10-13, 3-7), who have now lost four consecutive games. Josiah Strong added 13 points. Liam McChesney had three blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
